text: NA-100 Faisalabad-VI () is a constituency for the National Assembly of Pakistan. ==Members of Parliament== ===2018–2023: NA-106 Faisalabad-VI=== Election Member Party 2018 Rana Sanaullah Khan PML (N) === 2024–present: NA-100 Faisalabad-VI === Election Member Party 2024 Nisar Ahmad Jutt PTI == Election 2002 == General elections were held on 10 Oct 2002. Nisar Ahmad Jutt of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarian (PPPP) won by 58,855 votes. == Election 2008 == General elections were held on 18 Feb 2008. Chaudhry Saeed Iqbal of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarian (PPPP) won by 65,322 votes. == Election 2013 == General elections were held on 11 May 2013. Nisar Ahmad Jutt of PML-N won by 122,041 votes and became the member of National Assembly. == Election 2018 == General elections were held on 25 July 2018. == Election 2024 == General elections were held on 8 February 2024. Nisar Ahmad Jutt won the election with 131,980 votes. ==Related pages== *NA-99 Faisalabad-V *NA-101 Faisalabad-VII == Notes == == References == ==Other websites== * Election result's official website Category:Constituencies of Pakistan
